-- Postbank rises on talk of RBS bid interest: traders
-- 
-- Fri Feb 22, 2008 10:03am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/02/22/us-postbank-rbs-idUSL2239843220080222

 

 LONDON/FRANKFURT  (Reuters) - Shares in Germany's Deutsche Postbank ( DPBGn.DE ) rose 2 percent in late afternoon trade on Friday on market talk of bid interest from Royal Bank of Scotland (RBS) ( RBS.L ), traders said. 

 "We're hearing RBS for Deutsche Postbank at the 90 euro per share level," said one trader in London. Deutsche Postbank was not immediately available for comment. At 9:53 a.m. EST, Deutsche Postbank shares were 1.6 percent higher at 64.54 euros, the third-biggest gainers on Frankfurt's DAX  .GDAXI , which was down 1 percent. RBS was up 2.5 percent. (Reporting by Sitaraman Shankar, Patricia Nann, Andrea Lentz and  Jonathan Gould )